body:
The script build.psm1:
[build.psm1](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/master/build.psm1)
from instruction of building:
[Build PowerShell on Linux](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/master/docs/building/linux.md)
checks for supported distros or throws error for not supported ones:

` 
        if( -not(
            $environment.IsDebian -or
            $environment.IsUbuntu -or
            $environment.IsRedHatFamily -or
            $environment.IsSUSEFamily -or
            $environment.IsAlpine)
        ) {
            throw "The current OS : $($LinuxInfo.ID) is not supported for building PowerShell."
        }
    }`

apparently Linux Mint is based on Ubuntu, then if I commented out 'throw' statement I was available to build it on Linux Mint correctly.

